{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "These metrics are computed based on the distribution of topic words and provide a numerical score that indicates how diverse the words are in the topics.",
    "Ideally, for topics that are semantically different from each other, we expect the diversity scores to be close to 1.",
    "This is because diverse topics are more informative and useful for downstream applications such as document classification or information retrieval.",
    "In our experiments, we consider PUW, PJD, IRBO and, use implementation of topic diversity 13 given by [75].-Proportion of Unique Words (PUW) [19] is used to determine the percentage of unique words in a topic.",
    "A PUW score that is close to 0 indicates that the topic contains a lot of redundant words, while a score close to 1 suggests that the topic is more diverse and contains a wider variety of words.-The Average Pairwise Jaccard Diversity (PJD) [78] measures the average pairwise Jaccard distance between the topics."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
